inn1.comm: short on middle and leg, whipped away behind square leg, wide of fine leg, for a couple
good length on the off stump, closes the face and pushes it back to the bowler
gone! Full and wide, moved away, chased it, went for an expansive drive, got a thick edge and Haddin dived well to his left to snap a sharp one
short of a good length on the off, dropped into the off side, calls for a single, is sent back
fullish on the off, defended off the front foot in the direction towards cover
yorker length on the off, dug out into the leg side, end of a successful over, well done Bolly
lucky, short of a good length on the off stump, dabbed at it, got a thin edge just wide of leg stump and to the fine-leg boundary, nipped back in a touch
fullish on the off stump, pushed through to cover
back of a length on the off, rocks back and punches it short of the bowler
teasing length outside off and moving away, left alone to the keeper
almost had him, drew him forward and Shehzad was found wanting, good length on the off and appeared to hold its line, struck him just outside the line
back of a length on middle, defended back to the bowler
oversteps, gets to the pitch and pushes it back past the bowler wide of mid-off for a single
short outside off, pulls it wide of midwicket, completely mistimed but got it in the gap, gets a couple
good length on the off and moving back in, defended towards mid-on
slightly short on middle, drops it short of midwicket and calls for a single, is sent back
full and wide, eases it through to mid-off, just a firm push
bang on the off stump, gets forward and defends solidly, Bolly continues to look good
drags it onto the stumps, short of a good length outside off, gets a hint of inward movement, Younis plays at it, away from his body, gets a thin edge to clip the off stump

appeal for caught behind, that was an edge and the umpire didn't hear it, probing him outside off, tried to defend it off the front foot, moved away to take a thin edge straight to the keeper, Aleem Dar shook his head but the Australians were convinced. Misbah is lucky!
similar delivery but kept a little low, dabbed down to third man for a single
back of a length outside off, leaving the right hander, left alone
much fuller, on a driving length, pushed firmly to mid-off
on middle and off, darting back in, played gently to midwicket, good stuff from Australia
nice pace, around 137.1 kmph, slightly short on the off, opens the face to guide it wide of point for a single
shot! Full on the off stump, the bat turns in his hand as he tries to drive it down, but nicely timed, beats Clarke at mid-on and gets him his first boundary
swinging back in, on middle, punched towards cover
good length outside off, angling it away, held its line there, left alone
mistimes it this time, full and wide, plays it straight to mid-off as he tries to drive hard at it
back of a length on the off stump, drops it to point
beat the outside edge, slower offcutter, moved away to evade the bat as he prodded forward
back of a length outside off, punched off the back foot through cover for a single
slower one again, the offcutter bowled at 114.7 kmph, left alone
bringing it back in, pushed through to mid-off on the front foot
slower one again, charged down the track and just chipped it over the bowler, wide of mid-off who gives chase and fumbles to concede an extra run
128.2 kmph, good length on the off stump, defended short of cover
back of a length on the off stump, stands tall and dabs it to point
testing line outside off, reaches for it and plays it to cover
a little too wide, short outside off and moved away, Misbah let it go
slightly short on the off, dropped short of cover, he's taking his time here, well Pakistan are, slow going so far
brought it back in this time, bunts it to cover
slightly short outside off, guided off the back foot to point
short of a good length on the off, punched to mid-off
drive it well but straight to cover, pushed off the front foot, failed to beat the gap
almost pays off, full and wide, has a wild swing at it, trying to clear midwicket, ends up mistiming it to mid-on
restraining himself this time, irritating pace this from Bracken, 114.3 kmph, irritating for the batsman that is, left alone outside off
a touch quicker, fullish on the off stump, pushed through the line to mid-off
hitting a good length again, pushed off the front foot to cover
back of a length on middle, whipped away wide of square leg, two short of fine leg, come on, get a move-on
holding its line, gets behind it and drops it short of the bowler
back of a length outside off, holding its line, lets it go through
gave him the charge, nothing happened, bunted it back to the bowler, dropped it short seeing him come down
nicely done, bowled at 132.4 kmph, moved away sharply after landing just a fraction short outside off, left alone
full on the off stump, driven to long-on for a single
slightly short outside off, hangs his bat out and plays it to point
slower one bowled on a good length on middle, moved across and pushed it to mid-on
slower ball bowled slightly short on the off, dabbed to point off the front foot
finally, short outside off, rocked back and punched it between point and cover for three runs
fullish outside off, opens the way and slashes it straight to point
just wide of midwicket, stopped on him a little, landed on a length on middle, pushed at it and lobbed just wide of the fielder to add a couple to the score
legcutter, length ball outside off, came down the track and tried to drive it through the leg side, cut away to beat the outside edge, around 118 kmph
teasing him outside off stump, defended towards cover
good length outside off, gets forward and drops it short of cover
back of a length, accurate again, drops it dead wide of the pitch
a touch fuller, outside off, moves front and across and flicks it away wide of square leg for a couple
good length on the off, defended towards point
short of a length on middle, worked away to deep square leg
slightly short on middle, tries to defend it off the back foot,.gets an inside edge behind square, gets a single
really slow pitch this, slower one outside off, pushed wide of mid-on
slightly short on middle, tries to fend it away, is hit on the ribs and it rolls into the off side
good length on the off, defended off the front foot short of cover
short outside off, cut away but straight to point, we'll see many tidy overs today, anything in the range of 200 should be competitive
tossed it up, on the off stump, driven straight to midwicket
on leg stump, tries to clip it fine, brushes his pads on its way wide of fine leg for a couple
tossed up on middle, pushed through to deep midwicket for a couple
two more, full on the off, bends low and paddles it wide of fine leg
quicker one bowled short on the off, turned away to square leg
spun back in sharply, got behind and tickled it square
bowled at 129.2 kmph, flicked away to the short fine fielder
slightly slower one, fullish on the off, almost sucked him in, bowled at 122.8 kmph, pushed through it, tried to chip it over the in-field but fortunately mistimed it, fell short of mid-off
short of a length on middle, comes down the track and plays at it, gets an inside edge onto his pads
on middle and off, taps it towards cover, no intent there
fullish on the off stump, defended watchfully towards cover
slower one on the off, punched short of mid-off to steal a quick single
on middle and off, tries to paddle it fine, didn't connect, lobbed up off his pads
flighted on middle and leg, swept to fine leg
good length outside off, spun back in to strike him outside the line, gets a run
short outside off, gets back and drops it short of point
short on middle, whipped away wide of deep square leg for a couple
worked away into the leg side again but fine leg runs in to prevent the second
short of a length outside off, pushed towards point from the crease, played away from his body there
much straighter, bowled at 128 kmph, walks and defends it to midwicket
slower one, legcutter, at 112.5 kmph, defended into the off side
saw him coming down and dropped it short, fends it behind square for a single
slower one on the off, plenty of those in this game, pushed off the front foot to Clarke at point
short of a length on the off, pushed away to midwicket off the front foot
flatter on the off stump and spinning in, defended back to the bowler
gave it some air this time, defended cautiously on the pitch
full outside off, turned short of midwicket and scampered off for a single
short of a length on middle, paddled to square leg off the front foot
tossed up outside off, gets across and chips it just short of midwicket
had him interested for a bit there, got an inside edge onto his pads and lobbed up in front of Haddin who wasn't able to reach it
loopy, on middle and leg, at <9>90 kmph, worked away to square leg
runs, finally, short and wide, rocks back and cuts it behind point for three runs, 50 up for Pakistan
short on the off, punched off the back foot to long-on
a touch fuller, driven down the ground to long-on again
tossed up outside off, leans forward and defends
flighted outside off, spinning back in, chopped down to point off the back foot
thrown up outside off, pushed away wide of midwicket
moves across to negate the spin, turned away to midwicket
flighted on middle, reaches forward and turns it wide of midwicket for a single again
gets forward and paddles it behind square leg for one more
flatter, gets outside off to turn it away, rapped on the pads and rolls back to the bowler
quicker one on the off, dabbed to midwicket off the front foot
loopy outside off, paddled again, a bit of strain that shot, and all that for a single
short outside off and moving in, pushed back off the back foot
tossed up outside off, Misbah, expecting it to spin back in played inside the line, missed as it went on straight
shortish on middle, helped on its way to fine leg
quicker on the off stump, tapped to cover
first signs of aggression, charges down and clears mid-off, not as well timed but earns a couple, still three-an-over
short of a length on the off, defended into the leg side
slightly flatter, and quicker outside off, pushed off the front foot to cover
tossed up on the off stump, dropped short of midwicket, the crowd won't be liking this
quicker on middle and off, turned away wide of midwicket for a quick single
massive spin, shaped himself for a cut but ended up dabbing it just wide of the stumps
nicely done, fetched it from outside off and drove it wide of long-on for a couple
worked away wide of square leg
short outside off, gets back and bunts it to deep cover
short on middle, pulled away to deep square leg
first boundary in almost 17 overs, slower through the air, short outside off, rocks back and punches it hard between long-off and deep cover, firmly struck
flighted outside off, pushed through to deep cover, nicely done
thought of paddling it, but it was a little too wide, ended up dabbing it to point
tossed up outside off, pushed straight to cover
low full toss on the off stump, driven to long-off
poor ball, picking up now, short on middle, rocks back and pulls it powerfully between deep square leg and deep midwicket
tossed up on middle, lunges forward and pushes it back to the bowler
turned away into the leg side short of midwicket
full on the off stump, pushed back to the bowler
quickish outside off, gets across and turns it away to midwicket
flighted outside off, comes down and pushes it down to long-on
easily done, runs coming a little easily now, driven down to long-on again
flighted on the off stump, pushed down the ground for one more
tossed up outside off, gets across and paddles it to fine leg
fetches it from the off stump and pushes it away to midwicket
beat the outside edge, short on the off and zipped away to beat the outside edge as he prodded at it
dipping into the right hander, full on middle, pushed back to the bowler
flighted on the off, pushed off the front foot to cover

plumb, tossed up on middle, went for the sweep after three dot balls, tried to get it behind square, it straightened, he missed and was struck on the back pad in line with the stumps. Bowden raised his finger immediately
tossed up on the off stump, zips away, pushed to cover off the back foot
tossed up on middle and off, driven down the ground wide of long-off to get off the mark
bowled flattish on the off stump, driven down to long-on
paddle it wide of fine leg, moved well across and helped it on its way
fullish on the pads, clipped to deep square leg for a single
safe shot, plenty of gaps, came down the track and lofted it inside out over mid-off for three runs
two more, tickled down wide of fine leg, Malik has done well in his brief stay
short outside off, spinning in, cut away to point
flighted on the off stump, defended off the front foot to cover

ooh, almost short on middle, came on really slow, stopped on him, went for the pull, was a little early into the shot, got the top edge and Bracken at deep square leg was a little slow getting off the mark and it fell just short of him as he came running in
flighted outside off, pushes at it, thick outside edge wide of point
lands on middle, reaches forward and sweeps it between deep square leg and deep midwicket for a couple more
beaten by the spin! Short, shaped himself for a cut, spun back in prodigiously to beat the outside edge, in fact, it went over the off stump
tossed up on the off stump, pushed off the front foot
short on middle, whipped away wide of midwicket for a single
gave it air, on the off stump, driven down to long-on
dropped, dipped in, short of a good length outside off, reached forward to defend, spun in sharply to brush the glove on the way to the keeper who fumbled it
pushed off the front foot towards long-on for a single
tossed up outside off, driven firmly wide of deep cover for a couple to bring up the 100, Malik continues to impress
tossed up outside off, bends low and sweeps it powerfully wide of deep square leg, takes off one hand after striking it cleanly
pushed firmly down the ground to long-off
back of a length, chopped down to deep cover of the back foot
pushed away off the back foot wide of point for a single
on middle and off, tries to work it away, is hand on the pads outside the line
Malik is lucky, shapes up for a sweep but not with much conviction, takes the top edge and drops just short of Hauritz
flighted on the off, pushed into the leg side
short of a length on middle, worked away off the back foot wide of midwicket
short of a good length outside off, guided wide of point for a single
tempted him with a flighted one outside off, pushed to cover
quicker through the air, on middle, tickled behind square for a single
short on middle, worked away to deep square leg for a single
short on middle, dabbed wide of point for a single
slower legcutter, tries to chop it down, gets an under-edge wide of Haddin for a single
short on middle and off, at 133.1 kmph, gets an inside edge wide of Haddin
slower one on the off, legcutter again, punched to cover
legcutter again, bowled at 120.4 kmph, worked away wide of midwicket, fails to squeeze in a single
short of a length on middle, punched off the back foot to long-on
beats everything, slower through the air, just outside off and spun back in to beat him as he tried to work it away off the front foot, just missed the stumps and Haddin faied to collect
worked away off the front foot to square leg
tossed up outside off, dropped on the off side short of cover

his patience was tested and finally, when offered some flight, failed to resist the temptation. Landed full on the off stump, went for a mighty slog-sweep over midwicket, it spun in, took the top-edge and stuck safely in the palms of Ferguson at long-on
tossed up on middle, pushed to mid-off
good length on the off stump, defended just wide of short mid-on
good length on middle, gets across and pushes it to mid-on
goes after it, just a fraction full and his eyes light up, chips it over mid-off, wide of deep cover for a couple
back of a length on middle, defended into the leg side off the back foot
slower one outside off, cutting away, defended to point off the back foot, it's just wide of him and they get a single
short on middle and leg, tickled wide of square leg for a single
tossed up on the off, pushed back past Symonds who lets it through followed by midwicket and they allow them a single
short outside off, moves across and turns it away wide of deep midwicket for a couple more
flighted outside off, paddled down to short fine
he's off, short outside off, tries to cut it past point, gets a thick outside edge to the third-man boundary, the crowd is up
short on the off stump, makes room and punches it down to deep cover
full toss on the off stump, he looks determined here, remember is a full toss and he bunts it down to long-on
short of a good length on the off stump, defended with a straight bat off the back foot
slower one bowled full on middle, picked it up, drove it down the ground to long-on
powerfully struck, legcutter again, took it on the half-volley and drilled it wide of long-off, he didn't have to cover much ground there but it raced away
on middle and leg, flicked away wide of deep square leg, a risky second but thrown at the wrong end, towards Malik at the non-striker's end
legcutter, beaten this time, short of a good length outside off, fished for it, was almost done in by the movement
four more, short outside off, played deliberately, it appeared that way, opened the face at the last moment to get it really fine wide of the keeper and a diving third man
good length outside off and shaping away, left alone to the keeper
looked plumb, nipped back in from the off, he got forward to defend but was struck just in line, didn't get across enough and played with bat really close to pad
yorker length outside off, full, dug out towards deep cover for a single
short of a good length on the off, pushed off the front foot towards midwicket

came back in, just manages to get his bat down in time, gets an inside edge onto his pads, calls for a single, is sent back, but a little late, Clarke has a shy at the stumps but misses, and concedes overthrows, four of them, through the midwicket region. Would have been out had he scored a direct hit
back of a length outside off, guided to cover
beaten by the legcutter, bowled at 129.3 kmph, reached forward to defend but it spat away
short on middle, defended off the back foot to the bowler
coming back in, slightly short on leg stump, defended towards mid-on
kept low and pegged back the offstump, short of a good length bowled at 132 kmph, failed to get his bat down in time and timber!
fullish outside off and moved away, left alone to the keeper
on middle and leg, tries to fend it away, clips his thighs on the way to square leg
122.9 kmph, darting back in a touch, defended to point off the front foot
cut away after landing on a good length on middle and off, defended in front of cover
picked the length early, much quicker, bowled at 133.1 kmph, pulled it away wide of mid-on, didn't time it all that well, but well enough for it to reach the ropes
bringing it back on, gets a thick inside edge wide of square leg, sticks to a single
moved away, covered it well by getting across and pushing it to cover
short of a length outside off, dropped short of point on the back foot
full outside off, gets way outside the line to flick it towards square leg, is hit on the pads
fumble at third man, almost palms it to the ropes but gets it on the second attempt, just two taken, tried to work it away but got a thick edge as the ball cut away, lucky
beaten, angling in from slightly wide of the crease and gets it to shape away after landing on a good length as he prods at it
short of a good length outside off, held its line this time, left alone to the keeper
short of a length on the off, punched wide of the bowler for a single
probing him outside off, taps it towards cover, Arafat intent on giving his senior partner the strike
slightly short on middle and leg, pushed straight to midwicket
back of a length on the off, slow, at 110.4 kmph, dabbed short of point
slower one again, at 108.8 kmph, dropped short of point for a quick single
normal pace, around 130 kmph, driven straight to cover
slower one outside leg stump, turned to fine leg for a single
slower one bowled on a good length on leg stump, turned wide of deep square leg for a single to keep the strike
short outside off, chops it down short of point, doesn't get hold at all
slower one on middle, picked it, drove it firmly wide of a diving midwicket for a couple, wristily done
short outside off, tries to swing it away over midwicket, misses, Haddin fumbles and they sneak a bye
good length on the off, walks across and pushes it to mid-off
short of a good length outside off and moves away, makes no contact as he fishes for it
back of a length on middle and off, defended back to the bowler
back of a length on middle, dropped short of the bowler, decent pace, 131 kmph
slower offcutter, pushed wide of point for a single
slower ball bowled short of a good length outside off, tries to dab it past the keeper, can't beat him
short of a length outside off, kept a little low as he tried to chop it down, misses
keeping him quiet now, slower one again, tapped to cover, decides against the single

offcutter, appeal for caught-behind, there was certainly a deflection as he tried to drive it past the bowler, Haddin takes it bending low but Aleem Dar says no, we need a replay to confirm what happened
good length on middle and off, chips it just short of deep midwicket
shot! Slightly short on the off, swats it powerfully off the front foot well over the long-on boundary
back of a length, nudges it delicately wide of third man for a couple
back of a length outside off, dabbed straight to point, the powerplay is yet to come
slower one on middle and leg, pushed off the front foot wide of midwicket for a quick single
short and wide, tries to run it down to keep the strike, misses and admonishes himself
slower ball bowled short on the off, chopped down to Clarke at cover
slower one on the off, comes down and has a wild swing, ends up mistiming it just short of long-off
short on middle and leg, punched down to long-on
slower one on leg stump, tickled to short fine, bowled at 101.7 kmph
offcutter, short on the off and cut away, he made room, had a massive swat at it, got a thin edge that was put down by Haddin, or so I thought, apologies, as it bounced just before it got to him
on middle and leg, worked away behind square to keep the strike

gone! Big wicket! Short on middle, gets more bounce and is pacy, bowled at 135 kmph, goes for a mighty pull, gets the top edge as it comes on a little too quickly and North takes an easy catch at mid-on
straying on the pads, waits for it and clips it away really fine to the fine-leg boundary, important runs these
back of a length on the off stump, dropped short of cover
offcutter, tried to dab it down to third man, missed as it moved away
slower one again, pushed at it off the front foot, missed and Haddin took it low, the bowler appealed but Haddin shook his head this time, saying there was no nick
short of a good length on the off stump, punched to cover
on middle and off, pushed into the leg side
slower one bowled full outside off, driven to cover who fumbles to let them sneak single
slower one bowled full on middle and leg, worked away wide of midwicket
slower offcutter, defended to point, an unnecessary throw to the striker's end, concedes an overthrow, Watson the culprit, he was also responsible for the misfield early in the over
slower one bowled short outside off, dabbed wide of point, decides against the single after calling for it
quick, bowled at 140.6 kmph, full on the off, pushed off the front foot to mid-off
short on leg stump, tries to flick it away, hit high on the pads and they squeeze a leg bye
full and wide, tries to drive hard, mistimes it between cover and cover-point for a single
short outside leg stump and cut back in, tried to shuffle and work it behind square, was struck on the pads and high
swung away hard, in the slot from Bolly, full on the middle, picked it and swatted it over midwicket in the vacant gap for a boundary
slower ball bowled short outside off, makes room and chops it down to third man
pushed into the off side off the back foot
dropped, Watson's having a terrible day, slower one, has a wild swing, gets the top edge and Watson, after getting under it nicely, drops a sitter
worked away behind square off the front foot
gone this time! Identical shot, gets the top edge again but is unfortunate it's not Watson under it again, got it much straighter and Hauritz at mid-on shows his team-mate how it's done
gets it in the gap, they are inching towards 200 now, on middle, swung away over midwicket to beat long-on and deep midwicket
short of a good length outside off, opens the face to guide it behind point and wide of third man for a couple
change of pace, slower outside off, tries to swat it over the bowler's head, gets the top edge and Clarke at point takes an excellent catch running backwards
full on middle and leg, flicked away stylishly to deep square leg
Bollinger gets five!! The legcutter, bowled at around 135 kmph, landed on a good length on middle and cut away to beat the bat and clip off stump

inn2.comm: short of a good length outside off, moved away, guided down to third man, a loosener bowled at 129.8 kmph
edged and gone! Shoaib strikes! Short of a good length and moved away, he pushed at it, away from his body, got a thin edge straight to Akmal
teasing line outside off, bowled at 138.1 kmph, came back in just a touch, left alone
starts off well, picking up pace, Shoaib, this was 141.2 kmph, clipped away to square leg, misfield, and a single
good length outside off and holds its line, left alone by Watson
almost dragged it on, the quickest ball of the over, at 144.9 kmph, came back in this time, hung his bat out, was lucky to get an inside edge onto his pads
zipped away, probing line outside off and Watson lets it go
shaping away there, a touch fuller, gets his foot forward and defends to cover
good length on and outside off, consistently getting some movement away from the bat, left alone
and again, lands on a driving length on the off stump and zips away, Watson chooses to leave it be
fishes for it this time and is beaten, short of a good length, tries to run it down but the movement again beats the outside edge
beaten, pretends to let go but is found out, tried to prod at it away from his body, but it moved away, excellent start from Tanvir
beaten, bowled at 144.3 kmph, darted back in, landed outside off and moved back in sharply, he played inside the line to that one but had no clue about the pace or the swing

he's given him! Landed on a good length on middle and moved away just a touch, was rapped on the pads playing half-forward, was done in by the pace, couldn't get bat behind ball,was struck in line with off
bowled from wide of the crease on middle, defended to cover
banged in short on middle, tucks it away behind square for a single
punished, excellent shot under pressure, short and wide at 143.3 k mph, slashes it away wide of point for a boundary
banged in short on the off from wide of the crease, at 145.3 kmph, defended to point off the back foot
Clarke is away, straying on the pads, flicks it away with absolute easy through square leg for a boundary, poor ball first up in a new over
coming round the wicket, at 136.5 kmph on middle and leg, too straight, pushed gently between midwicket and mid-on for two more
angling in and he leaves it riskily, came back in just a touch and it went over the off stump, would have been an embarassing dismissal had the crashed into the stumps
short of a good length on the off, punched back towards mid-on, did so solidly
takes the outside edge, angling in and moved it away, dabbed at it, got a thick edge wide of slip to third man
short outside off, held its line this time, guided down to third man to keep the strike
good length on the off, bowled at 145 kmph, punched to Afridi at cover
angling into the right hander, came forward to defend, rockets in at 146.6 kmph, came back in to strike him high on the thighs, Aleem Dar thinks he got an inside edge, we'll have to wait and see
on middle and off, dabs hard at it, gets it wide of square leg for a couple
short of a good length on the off, gets forward and defends it solidly to cover
inside edge on the pads and rolls just wide of leg stump, pushed at it on the up but didn't get to the pitch and it came onto him a little too quickly, at 147.6 kmph
good length on middle and leg, defended to midwicket
full on middle and leg, driven wide of midwicket for a single
slightly short outside off, tapped wide of point for a quick single
left him and he leaves it be, shaping it away from him, back to over the wicket now
fuller and Clarke lets it go confidently, knew where his offstump was, leaves it alone as it moves away
on middle and off, held its line, pushed through to mid-off on the front foot
swings hard, picked the slower one, bowled at 117.4 kmph, tried to dispatch it over mid-on but it cut back in to beat the bat
powerfully hit, waited for it, got to the pitch and drove it stylishly through the covers, raced away
much straighter, at 145.5 kmph on middle, defended back to the bowler
short of a good length outside off, negotiated easily, dabbed down to third man
full and wide, Clarke isn't tempted, lets it go through
the quickest ball of the game, hitting 148.2 kmph, a little too wide though, Clarke doesn't bother
good length on middle and leg, defended back to the bowler on the front foot
back of a length outside off, chopped down through the slips down to third man

excellent shot, was not quite to the pitch but played it with a straight bat, bowled on a good length on middle and off, he gets forward and drives it through the line past the bowler and wide of mid-off
moved away this time, short of a good length, chased it but was beaten by the movement
takes a couple of steps and punches it past the bowler to mid-off
pushed firmly to cover off the front foot, drawing him forward but he tackles it well. calls for a single but it isn't there
on middle and leg, turned wide of midwicket where Shehzad dives and saves a run
pushed back to the bowler off the front foot
short and wide, tries to cut it past point from the crease, it zips through to beat the outside edge
beaten! Bowled at 136.7 kmph, cut away to beat the outside edge as he came forward to block
on middle and off, gets back and punches it down to mid-on
cut back in this time, defended off the back foot respectfully to the bowler
probing line outside off, at 130 kmph, left alone
in the slot and Clarke is upset he missed out, full on middle and leg, should have driven it wide of midwicket but he failed to find the gap
superb shot, full on the off, another length ball, walks forward and just eases it past mid-off, compensates well for the missed opportunity the previous ball
